com.ebay.redlasersdk
Class BarcodeResult

java.lang.Object
  com.ebay.redlasersdk.BarcodeResult
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.os.Parcelable, java.io.Serializable
public class BarcodeResult
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable, java.io.Serializable

Results from the SDK are delivered as members of this class. The SDK delivers a Collection of barcodes recognized during a scanning session, both to the status update method (which is called several times per second) and to the calling activity when scanning completes.

Field Detail

barcodeType

public int barcodeType
The type of barcode found. Will be one of the types listed in BarcodeTypes.

barcodeString

public java.lang.String barcodeString
Text of the barcode. This is the character string read from the barcode, without additional processing. This means that Code 128 and QR Code barcodes may have AI and DI markers, and the optional checksum character in Code 39 barcodes will be returned if present. See the pdf documentation on specific barcode types for more information on specific symbologies.

extendedBarcodeString

public java.lang.String extendedBarcodeString
Extended barcode string. Currently only used for UPC-E barcodes; this will contain the expanded EAN-13 equivalent string.

firstScanTime

public java.util.Date firstScanTime
Timestamp of the initial recognition of this barcode.

mostRecentScanTime

public java.util.Date mostRecentScanTime
Timestamp of the most recent time this barcode was recognized. While scanning, this value will keep updating with the current time as long as the SDK can see the barcode.

uniqueID

public java.util.UUID uniqueID
A unique ID for this object instance; used by associatedBarcode

associatedBarcode

public java.util.UUID associatedBarcode
Refers to the uniqueID field of a barcode that is associated with this barcode. See the pdf documentation on associated barcodes.

barcodeLocation

public java.util.ArrayList<android.graphics.PointF> barcodeLocation
Barcode location in the coordinate system of the preview view. This is a list of points defining the corners of the barcode. The first point in the array is the top left corner of the barcode. The second point in the array is the top right corner of the barcode.

The list is NOT guaranteed to contain 4 points, the polygon it defines is not guaranteed to wind clockwise, and is not guaranteed to be convex. It is guaranteed to be a simple polygon.

If a barcode is recognized upside-down in the viewfinder, the first point in the array will be the bottom-right of the returned points. This is because that point is the top-left corner of the barcode in its natural orientation. Similarly, when using the front camera, the first point will be to the right of the second point when scanning a barcode right side up, and the points will wind counterclockwise, since the camera preview is mirrored along the Y axis when using the front camera.

isPartialBarcode

public boolean isPartialBarcode
TRUE if this is an incomplete barcode result. Some barcodes may be recognized in parts by scanning the device across the length of the barcode; see the pdf documentation. The barcodeString field of a partial barcode will contain an initial substring of the final barcode string.

CREATOR

Part of the Parcelable interface. BarcodeResults get returned to the calling Activity via a return Intent.

BarcodeResult

Parameters:

BarcodeResult

public BarcodeResult(BarcodeResult copyFrom)
Copy Constructor. Deep copies anything mutable. BarcodeResults have several mutable fields--mostRecentScanTime for example will continually update as long as the barcode is visible. Results that arrive in a particular status update have been copy constructed; the SDK won't change values of members of that particular instance later. The next call to the status method will deliver a new copy of the same result.

getAssociatedBarcode

public BarcodeResult getAssociatedBarcode(java.util.AbstractCollection<BarcodeResult> resultSet)

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
For BarcodeResults, instances that have the same barcodeSting and barcodeType are considered equal. This is done to make inserting barcodeResults into sets work correctly.

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object

hashCode

public int hashCode()
BarcodeResult overrides equals, so it must override hashCode. BarcodeResults hash to the same value if and only if their barcodeType and barcodeString fields match. Other fields are not part of the hash.
